
The Ashy-crowned Sparrow-lark (Eremopterix griseus) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family. It is found in Bangladesh, India, Nepal, Pakistan, and Sri Lanka.
Source

BirdLife International 2004. Eremopterix griseus. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Downloaded on 24 July 2007.


